refsect2.variablelist:
-p/--properties PROPERTIES...
Gets the value of one or more properties.
It is possible to access sub properties with a / between each property. For example: "property1/property2/property3" would try to access the value "foo" in the following schema:
<dm:property1> <dm:property2> <dm:property3>foo</dm:property3> </dm:property2> </dm:property1>
If no property was specified, DocManager reads the data of all properties (including sub properties). &optionalopt;
--format FORMAT
Set the output format. Valid format types: table, json, xml
The default is plain text. &optionalopt;
--quiet/-q
This will reduce the output to the minimum. By default, you get also an overview over all XML errors. &optionalopt;
&filesentry;
